Definition: patronymic from {{h7748}}; a Shuchamite (collectively); Shuhamites.
from {{h7743}}; humbly; Shucham, an Israelite; Shuham.
a primitive root; to sink, literally or figuratively; bow down, incline, humble.
a primitive root; to muse pensively; meditate.
from the same as {{h7740}} and the dual of {{h7151}}; plain of a double city; Shaveh-Kirjathajim, a place East of the Jordan; Shaveh Kiriathaim.
from {{h7737}}; plain; Shaveh, a place in Palestine; Shaveh.
patronymic from {{h7744}}; a Shuchite or descendant of Shuach; Shuhite.
the same as {{h7745}}; Shuchah, an Israelite; Shuah.
from {{h7743}}; a chasm; ditch, pit.
from {{h7743}}; dell; Shuach, a son of Abraham; Shuah.
or (feminine) שׂוֹכָה; from {{h7753}}; a branch (as interleaved); bough.
or שֹׂכֹה; or שׂוֹכוֹ; from {{h7753}}; Sokoh or Soko, the name of two places in Palestine; Shocho, Shochoh, Sochoh, Soco, Socoh.
probably patronymic from a name corresponding to {{h7754}} (feminine); a Sukathite or descendant of an unknown Israelite named Sukah; Suchathite.
from an unused root meaning to hang down; a skirt; by implication, a bottom edge; hem, skirt, train.
or (by permutation) סוּט; a primitive root; to detrude, i.e. (intransitively and figuratively) become derelict (wrongly practise; namely, idolatry); turn aside to.

a primitive root; properly, to push forth; (but used only figuratively) to lash, i.e. (the sea with oars) to row; by implication, to travel; go (about, through, to and fro), mariner, rower, run to and fro.
from {{h7751}}; a lash (literally or figuratively); scourge, whip.
a primitive root; to entwine, i.e. shut in (for formation, protection or restraint); fence, (make an) hedge (up).
or שֵׁילָל; (Micah 1:8), from {{h7997}}; nude (especially bare-foot); by implication, captive; spoiled, stripped.
from {{h7999}}; peaceful (with the article always prefixed, making it a pet name); the Shulammith, an epithet of Solomon's queen; Shulamite.
the same as {{h7799}}; Shushan, a place in Persia; Shushan.
from an unused root (akin to {{h5375}} and {{h7722}}) meaning to rise; a rising; arise.
from the same as {{h5469}}; a round pendant for the neck; ornament, round tire like the moon.

or שַׁו; from the same as {{h7722}} in the sense of desolating; evil (as destructive), literally (ruin) or morally (especially guile); figuratively idolatry (as false, subjective), uselessness (as deceptive, objective; also adverbially, in vain); false(-ly), lie, lying, vain, vanity.
or (feminine) שׁוֹאָה; or שֹׁאָה; from an unused root meaning to rush over; a tempest; by implication, devastation; desolate(-ion), destroy, destruction, storm, wasteness.

a primitive root; to turn back (hence, away) transitively or intransitively, literally or figuratively (not necessarily with the idea of return to the starting point); generally to retreat; often adverbial, again; ((break, build, circumcise, dig, do anything, do evil, feed, lay down, lie down, lodge, make, rejoice, send, take, weep)) × again, (cause to) answer (  again), × in any case (wise), × at all, averse, bring (again, back, home again), call (to mind), carry again (back), cease, × certainly, come again (back), × consider,   continually, convert, deliver (again),   deny, draw back, fetch home again, × fro, get (oneself) (back) again, × give (again), go again (back, home), (go) out, hinder, let, (see) more, × needs, be past, × pay, pervert, pull in again, put (again, up again), recall, recompense, recover, refresh, relieve, render (again), requite, rescue, restore, retrieve, (cause to, make to) return, reverse, reward,   say nay, send back, set again, slide back, still, × surely, take back (off), (cause to, make to) turn (again, self again, away, back, back again, backward, from, off), withdraw.
from the same as {{h7723}}; false; Sheva, an Israelite; Sheva.
the same as {{h7726}}; rebellious; Shobab, the name of two Israelites; Shobab.
from {{h7725}}; apostate, i.e. idolatrous; backsliding, frowardly, turn away (from margin).
from {{h7725}}; a return; returning.
from {{h7725}}; apostate, i.e. heathenish or (actually) heathen; backsliding.
from the same as {{h7640}}; overflowing; Shobal, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites; Shobal.
active participle from a primitive root meaning to leave (compare {{h7662}}); forsaking; Shobek, an Israelite; Shobek.
for {{h5441}}; a thicket, i.e. interlaced branches; thick boughs.
perhaps for {{h7730}}; Shobak, a Syrian; Shobach.
a primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. figuratively (by implication of insolence) to devastate; waste.

a primitive root; properly, to level, i.e. equalize; figuratively, to resemble; by implication, to adjust (i.e. counterbalance, be suitable, compose, place, yield, etc.); avail, behave, bring forth, compare, countervail, (be, make) equal, lay, be (make, a-) like, make plain, profit, reckon.
a primitive root; to retreat; turn back.
a primitive root; to hedge in; make to grow.
a primitive root; to destroy; × substance (from the margin).
(Aramaic); corresponding to {{h7737}}; to resemble; make like.
apparently from {{h7704}}; a cultivated field; blasted, field.
plural from the same as {{h7704}}; flats; Siddim, a valley in Palestine; Siddim.
from the same as {{h7704}} and {{h217}}; spreader of light; Shedejur, an Israelite; Shedeur.
from {{h7703}}; the Almighty; Almighty.
from {{h7703}}; a wife (as mistress of the house); × all sorts, musical instrument.
or שָׂדַי; from an unused root meaning to spread out; a field (as flat); country, field, ground, land, soil, × wild.
a primitive root; properly, to be burly, i.e. (figuratively) powerful (passively, impregnable); by implication, to ravage; dead, destroy(-er), oppress, robber, spoil(-er), × utterly, (lay) waste.
a primitive root; to abrade, i.e. harrow a field; break clods, harrow.
or שׁוֹד; (Job 5:21), from {{h7736}}; violence, ravage; desolation, destruction, oppression, robbery, spoil(-ed, -er, -ing), wasting.
a primitive root (identical with {{h7786}} through the idea of reducing to pieces; compare {{h4883}}); to saw; cut.
a primitive root; properly, to vanquish; by implication, to rule (causatively, crown); make princes, have power, reign. See {{h5493}}.
from {{h7783}}; the (lower) leg (as a runner); hip, leg, shoulder, thigh.
from {{h7783}}; a street (as run over); street.
a primitive root; to run after or over, i.e. overflow; overflow, water.
or שֹׁפָר; from {{h8231}} in the original sense of incising; a cornet (as giving a clear sound) or curved horn; cornet, trumpet.
patronymic from {{h8197}}; a Shuphamite (collectively) or descendants of Shephupham; Shuphamite.
from {{h8210}}; poured; Shophak, a Syrian; Shophach.

a primitive root (identical with through the idea of going round for inspection); to spy out, i.e. (generally) survey, (for evil) lurk for, (for good) care for; behold, lay wait, look, observe, perceive, regard, see.
a primitive root; properly, to turn, i.e. travel about (as a harlot or a merchant); go, singular See also {{h7891}}.
from an unused root probably mean to blanch; a gem, probably the beryl (from its pale green color); onyx.
the same as {{h7718}}; Shoham, an Israelite; Shoham.
a primitive root; to scorch; blast.
or שִׁדָּפוֹן; from {{h7710}}; blight; blasted(-ing).
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to endeavor; labour.
from an unused root meaning to regulate; a row, i.e. rank (of soldiers), story (of rooms); board, range.
probably of foreign origin; Shadrak, the Babylonian name of one of Daniel's companions; Shadrach.
(Aramaic) the same as {{h7714}}; Shadrach.
or שֵׂי; probably from {{h7582}} through the idea of pushing out to graze; a member of a flock, i.e. a sheep or goat; (lesser, small) cattle, ewe, goat, lamb, sheep. Compare {{h2089}}.
from an unused root meaning to testify; a witness; record.
from {{h7889}}; a foe (as lying in wait); enemy.
from {{h7788}}; a wall (as going about); wall.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7791}}; wall.
the same as {{h7791}}; Shur, a region of the Desert; Shur.
from {{h7788}}; a bullock (as a traveller); bull(-ock), cow, ox, wall (by mistake for {{h7791}}).
from {{h7786}} in the primitive sense of {{h5493}}; properly, a ring, i.e. (by analogy) a row (adverbially); principal.
the same as {{h8321}}; a vine; Sorek, a valley in Palestine; Sorek.
or שִׂישׂ; a primitive root; to be bright, i.e. cheerful; be glad, × greatly, joy, make mirth, rejoice.
from {{h7797}}; joyful; Shavsha, an Israelite; Shavsha.

or שׁוֹשָׁן; or שֹׁשָׁן; and (feminine) שׁוֹשַׁנָּה; from {{h7797}}; a lily (from its whiteness), as a flower of architectural ornament; also a (straight) trumpet (from the tubular shape); lily, Shoshannim.
from {{h7768}}; a halloo; cry, riches.
a primitive root; properly, to be free; but used only causatively and reflexively, to halloo (for help, i.e. freedom from some trouble); cry (aloud, out), shout.
patronymic from {{h7764}}; a Shunite (collectively) or descendants of Shuni; Shunites.
from an unused root meaning to rest; quiet; Shuni, an Israelite; Shuni.
patrial from {{h7766}}; a Shunammitess, or female inhabitant of Shunem; Shunamite.
probably from the same as {{h7764}}; quietly; Shunem, a place in Pal; Shunem.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7760}}; command, give, lay, make,   name,   regard, set.

or שִׂים; a primitive root; to put (used in a great variety of applications, literal, figurative, inferentially, and elliptically); × any wise, appoint, bring, call (a name), care, cast in, change, charge, commit, consider, convey, determine,   disguise, dispose, do, get, give, heap up, hold, impute, lay (down, up), leave, look, make (out), mark,   name, × on, ordain, order,   paint, place, preserve, purpose, put (on),   regard, rehearse, reward, (cause to) set (on, up), shew,   stedfastly, take, × tell,   tread down, (over-)turn, × wholly, work.
or שֹׁמֵר; active participle of {{h8104}}; keeper; Shomer, the name of two Israelites; Shomer.
from an unused root meaning to exhale; garlic (from its rank odor); garlic.
or שֹׁעֵר active participle of {{h8176}} (as denominative from {{h8179}}); a janitor; doorkeeper, porter.
a primitive root; properly, to gape, i.e. snap at; figuratively, to overwhelm; break, bruise, cover.
or שֻׁעָל; from the same as {{h8168}}; a jackal (as a burrower); fox.
the same as {{h7776}}; Shual, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine; Shual.
from {{h7768}}; wealth; Shua, an Israelitess; Shua.
feminine of {{h7773}}; a hallooing; crying.
the same as {{h7771}}; rich; Shoa, an Oriental people; Shoa.
from {{h7768}}; a halloo; cry.
the same as {{h7769}}; Shua, a Canaanite; Shua, Shuah.
from {{h7768}} in the original sense of freedom; a noble, i.e. liberal, opulent; also (as noun in the derived sense) a halloo; bountiful, crying, rich.
